After fetching a copy of this app:

1. Create a config/database.yml file, you can base it on config/database.yml.example
2. Unless using SQLite, create the databases you specified in config/database.yml
3. Bring your new databases up to date:
    rake db:migrate
4. Install the necessary gems listed in config/environment.rb:
    [sudo] rake gems:install
5. Verify that all the tests pass:
    rake [test]
        or
    rake spec
